This file is generated by running `python code/data/save_dataset.py`.
The content is binary HDF5 data created by the `save_to_hdf5` function.
It contains the cleaned polymer graphs from the NIST/PubChem ingestion pipeline.
Structure:
- /dataset/graphs/{id}/nodes_json
- /dataset/graphs/{id}/edges_json
- /dataset/graphs/{id}/attrs (smiles, molecular_weight, etc.)
- /dataset/stats (count, average_molecular_weight)

To verify:
import h5py
with h5py.File('code/data/processed/polymers.h5', 'r') as f:
    print(f.keys())
    print(f['dataset/stats'].attrs['count'])